div.p:
Lieut. Fox, of Admiral Skerrett’s staff, furnishes me the following information,
                    in the shape of a memorandum, showing the movements of American troops to and
                    from American vessels in Honolulu:

Americans number 1,928; natives and half-castes, 40,612; Chinese, 15,301;
                    Japanese, 12,360; Portuguese, 8,602; British, 1,344; Germans, 1,034; French, 70;
                    Norwegians, 22 Polynesians, 588, and other foreigners, 419.

The minister of finance informs me that the taxes paid by Americans and Europeans
                    amount to $274,516.74; those by natives, $71,386.82; half-castes, $26,868.68;
                    Chinese, $87,366.10; Japanese, $67,326.07; other nationalities, $729.82.
